claim.claim-text:
6. A method of, at a User Equipment (UE), processing physical downlink control channel signals in a wireless communication system, the method comprising:
receiving one or more Physical Downlink Control Channels (PDCCHs) and one or more Physical Hybrid ARQ Channels (PHICHs) using interleaved N Control Channel Elements (CCEs), wherein each of the one or more PDCCHs carries Downlink Control Information (DCI) and each of the one or more PHICHs carries Hybrid ARQ Acknowledgement (HARQ-ACK);
de-interleaving the N CCEs in units of a Resource Element Group (REG);
de-mapping the one or more PDCCHs from first L CCEs of the N CCEs, wherein L≧1; and
de-mapping the one or more PHICHs from last M CCEs of the N CCEs, wherein M=N−L≧1 and wherein each CCE includes 9 consecutive REGs, and each REG includes 4 neighboring available Resource Elements (REs) in an Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing (OFDM) symbol.
